hivis.data

Class DataSetDefault

  • java.lang.Object
    • hivis.data.DataSetDefault
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    DataSet
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AbstractDataSeries, AbstractDataTable

    public class DataSetDefault
extends Object
implements DataSet
    Default base class for any object representing a set of data. For example a vector, table or graph. It provides some basic data storage (name, container DataSet) as well as a framework for handling changes to DataSets (see beginChanges(Object), setDataChanged(Object) and finishChanges(Object).
    Author:
    O. J. Coleman

      • setDataChanged

        public void setDataChanged(Object changeType)
        All subclasses should call this method whenever the data is modified in some way. This method should not generally be called by non-subclasses. If a container is set then the change will be registered with it too. If no object has registered that it is making multiple changes via beginChanges(Object) then a DataChangeEvent will be fired (see addChangeListener(DataListener)).
        Specified by:
        setDataChanged in interface DataSet

      • getCurrentChangers

        public List<Object> getCurrentChangers()
        Description copied from interface: DataSet
        Get the list of objects that are currently changing the data, if any. A list is used for getCurrentChangers() so that duplicates may occur. This in order to handle cases such as a process changing a DataTable calling beginChanges() on the DataTable, and then beginChanges() on the individual DataSeries of the DataTable (resulting in more calls to beginChanges on the container DataTable) before calling finishChanges on the DataSeries and then the DataTable. In each call to finishChanges only one of the occurrences of the DataTable will be removed.
        Specified by:
        getCurrentChangers in interface DataSet
        See Also:
        #beginChanges(Object, Object)
